      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SERGEANT DUKER (5) made a big impression on debut when hit the ground running from the squeeze draw with a fast early split, paving the way for a 1.5 lengths win at this track over 400m in 23.09. Promising type and rates to win again. ZIPPING PERCAT (8) started at long odds last time but ran well above expectations, breaking through for a maiden win by a neck at Gunnedah over 527m (30.88). Boxed wide here. Yet to win at the journey but has run some good races. Bold showing expected again. KAELIX NITRO (7) finds it hard to win but looks close to breaking through. Filled a minor placings again last time when third (30.25) at Gosford making it three placings in a row. Can feature again. SHINING GIRL (4) can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
